doc.after: According to the former chair of Israel's Knesset Foreign Affairs and Defense Committee, Yuval Steinitz, the Egyptian Air Force has roughly the same number of modern warplanes as the Israeli Air Force and far more Western tanks, artillery, anti-aircraft batteries and warships than the IDF.[127] Egypt is speculated by Israel to be the second country in the region with a spy satellite, EgyptSat 1[128] in addition to EgyptSat 2 launched on 16 April 2014.[129]
